---
title: Lauranne Paulissen | Actrice | Theatermaker
---

<div class="mx-auto w-full border-b-[12px] border-[#FFEBF4] md:px-20 lg:px-40 md:mt-12">
  <img src="<%= image_path(data.pages.home.hero.image) %>" alt="Lauranne Paulissen" class="w-full">
</div>


<div class="text-center text-xl md:text-2xl pt-12 font-light">
  VOLGENDE VOORSTELLINGEN
</div>

<div class="px-4 mt-4">
  <div class="table w-full">
    <% data.pages.martha.performances.select { |performance| performance.date && performance.date > Date.today }.sort_by { |performance| performance.date }.each do |performance| %>
      <a class="table-row border-b border-gray-200 hover:bg-gray-100" href="<%= performance.link %>">
        <div class="table-cell py-2 px-4">
          <span class="font-semibold mr-2 block md:inline"><%= performance.date.strftime("%d.%m.%Y") %></span>
          <span>Martha de Krankzinnige - <%= performance.time %> <%= performance.venue %></span>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell text-right px-4 py-2 align-bottom underline"><% if performance.link.present? %>tickets<% end %></div>
      </a>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>




<div class="text-center text-xl md:text-2x mt-24 font-light">
  PROJECTEN
</div>

<div class="mt-4 pb-10 px-4 grid grid-cols-1 gap-12">
  <% 3.times do %>
    <div class="bg-[#FFEBF4] rounded-[20px] px-8 py-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 sm:gap-0">
      <div class="px-4 min-w-56 lg:min-w-64">
        <%= image_tag 'uploads/skull.jpg', resize: '600x600', alt: 'forgotten female playwrights', class: "object-cover" %>
      </div>

      <div class="px-4 pr-8 col-span-4">
        Repertoire theatre is at odds with the current diversity debate. The texts and the portrayal of those pieces on stage, are often not inclusive enough: besides an acute shortage for complex roles for minorities, other identity markers (ability, age, ethnicity, skin color, gender,..) arenâ€™t always considered when working with the dramatic repertoire. However, in the wake of #MeToo and Black Lives Matter a change seems to occur: art schools and the theatre landscape are looking for a thorough reformation of repertoire theatre according to the needs of our current society.
      </div>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</div>

